President Jacob Zuma raised concerns about certain submissions regarding the constitutionality of the bill. JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma has referred the Financial Intelligence Centre Amendment Bill (Fica Bill) back to the National Assembly for reconsideration. The Presidency has released a statement saying that Zuma is concerned about certain submissions regarding the constitutionality of the bill.He has specifically raised concerns with the provisions relating to warrantless searches, which according to him, fall short of the constitutional standard required for the provision not to unjustifiably limit the right to privacy.More to follow on this developing story.